---
import SectionLayout from '../../layouts/SectionLayout.astro';

const title = 'Privacy Policy';
const description =
  'Privacy Policy for ErrorCodesIndex.com describing data handling, logs, cookies, advertising, and contact submissions in a static documentation site context.';
const crumbs = [
  { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
  { label: 'Privacy Policy', href: '/privacy-policy/' },
];
---

<SectionLayout title={title} description={description} crumbs={crumbs}>
  <p>Effective date: {new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10)}</p>

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    ErrorCodesIndex.com is a static reference website. We do not offer user accounts. We do not sell products.
    Information collected is limited to what is necessary to operate the site, ensure security, and respond to inbound
    messages.
  </p>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Server and security logs</strong>: IP address, user agent, timestamp, request URL, and related diagnostic
      information that may be recorded by our hosting and CDN providers.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Contact form submissions</strong>: name, email address, and message content when you contact us.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Cookies and similar technologies</strong>: may be used by analytics or advertising services (if enabled)
      for measurement and fraud prevention.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we use information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Operate and secure the website.</li>
    <li>Respond to requests and messages you submit.</li>
    <li>Measure site reliability and performance.</li>
    <li>Support advertising and related compliance requirements, if advertising is enabled.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Advertising</h2>
  <p>
    We may display advertising on the site. Advertising partners may use cookies or similar identifiers to measure ad
    performance, limit frequency, and reduce fraud. If you are located in a region with additional consent
    requirements, ads may be served using a consent framework.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-party services</h2>
  <p>
    Our hosting provider and related infrastructure services (such as CDN, DNS, or security tooling) may process
    request metadata to deliver pages and protect the site. Contact form submissions may be processed by our hosting
    platform’s forms feature.
  </p>

  <h2>Data retention</h2>
  <p>
    We retain contact submissions only as long as necessary to address the request and maintain reasonable records.
    Infrastructure logs are retained according to provider policies.
  </p>

  <h2>Your choices</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>You can avoid submitting personal information by not using the contact form.</li>
    <li>You can control cookies through your browser settings and, where applicable, consent controls.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For privacy-related questions, use the contact page. Include “Privacy” in the message subject.
  </p>
</SectionLayout>

